                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso)" facs="001 002"/>
                    Gäbrä Mädḫǝn, in blue ink
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002"/>
                    a note on the Psalms of David
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#71v"/>
                    Three full-stop symbols mark the midpoint of the psalms
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    Binding is original and mostly intact. Only a couple of chain stitches are compromised
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    The general condition of the vellum is good. Some discoloration and cracking is visible
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–20
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                      Scribal intervention:
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#18r #27v #36r #50r"/>, etc.);
                      lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#5v #9r #43r #45r"/>, etc.); and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#126r"> f. 126r, line 10</locus>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#32r"/>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#29r #39r #54r"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                      This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for the width of most lines. On a few occasions, the line would have been too long and the scribe finishes the end of the line with words written smaller so as to avoid leftover text (e.g., <locus target="#15v #20r #21v"/>). Occasionally a line is still too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the line (e.g., <locus target="#8v #16r #19r"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
